  "What does 'weighting' mean in polling?": "",
  "Adjusting for demographic imbalances in the sample compared to the population": "",
  "Measuring the physical weight of survey forms": "",
  "Giving more importance to the largest poll": "",
  "Removing outlier responses from the data": "",
  "Weighting adjusts the data so that underrepresented groups count more and overrepresented groups count less, making the sample more representative of the actual population.": "",
  "What is a 'tracking poll'?": "",
  "A poll with no margin of error reported": "",
  "A poll that repeatedly surveys over time to detect changes in opinion": "",
  "A poll that uses only one question": "",
  "A poll conducted only once during a campaign": "",
  "Tracking polls survey at regular intervals (often daily or weekly) to follow trends and detect shifts in public opinion over time.": "",
  "What does 'nonresponse bias' mean?": "",
  "Bias from having too many respondents": "",
  "Bias that occurs when people who do not respond differ systematically from those who do": "",
  "Bias caused by asking too many questions": "",
  "Bias caused by using random sampling": "",
  "Nonresponse bias occurs when the people who choose not to participate have different opinions or characteristics than those who do, skewing the results.": "",
